The article highlights the need for worker power in the United States to address the challenges of the pandemic, economic crisis, and racial disparities. It emphasizes the importance of creating an economy that benefits everyone, particularly workers of color and women who have faced discrimination and exclusion. The President is calling on Congress to create new union jobs in clean energy, infrastructure, care, manufacturing, and research. The plan aims to empower workers, create good jobs, and ensure that employers follow labor standards and remain neutral when employees seek to organize a union. The plan also aims to connect workers with good jobs both now and in the future.